examples: The mind is the actuator of the body.

definitions.definition: A usually electric device that causes a mechanical device (i.e., a mechanism ) to be switched on or off. For example; an electric motor that opens and closes a valve .
The mechanism that moves the head assembly on a disk drive .
A relay that controls the flow of electricity.

secondary_definitions: A usually electric device that causes a mechanical device (i.e., a mechanism ) to be switched on or off. For example; an electric motor that opens and closes a valve .
( computer hardware ) The mechanism that moves the head assembly on a disk drive .
( electrical ) A relay that controls the flow of electricity.
